summary:
I am an energetic woman with a passion for people. I am curious, an avid reader and a life long learner. Words that other people use to describe me are: warm, open, grounded, friendly, calm, wise, deep, a helper, a sharp observer and a true professional. 

My life purpose is to inspire people to connect with themselves and with others, in order to create a better understanding. In a business context this takes shape through developing leaders. By living my life purpose I want to contribute to a better world for all.

My life and work are guided by my values: Love, warmth, respect, integrity and freedom. It is my fundamental belief that all people are naturally creative, resourceful and whole; from this perspective I coach, train, consult and facilitate.

My specialties: 
- Leadership development
- Organizational development
- (Co-Active) Coaching
- Personal development
- Learning & development
- Instructional design
- MBTI
- Hay Emotional and Social Competency Inventory
- Cultural Transformation Tools (Barrett Values Center)

volunteer_experiences.description: The International Coach Federation (ICF) is the largest worldwide resource for professional coaches and the source for those who are seeking a coach. ICF campaigns worldwide for professional standards within the coaching profession, and provides independent certification for professional coaches and coach training programs. ICF is advancing the coaching profession so coaching becomes an integral part of society. Its members lead this journey by representing the highest quality in professional coaching. ICF Netherlands represents ICF Global in the Netherlands.
